    md("# Task 5 - Executive Presentation and Regulatory Submission\n## AI-Augmented Business Analyst Capstone\n**Company:** Meridian Financial | **Scenario:** FCA KYC/AML Onboarding Remediation\n---\n## Overview\nSarah Chen needs two things for the 6-week FCA deadline: (1) a 2-3 page executive summary for Marcus Reid (CFO), and (2) a 10-slide presentation for the FCA Supervision team.\n\n**Key Dates:**\n- Sprint 1 End: +10 weeks\n- FCA 90-Day Deadline: +12 weeks\n\n## Deliverables\n1. Executive Summary (2-3 pages)\n2. 10-slide FCA presentation deck\n3. Q&A Preparation Brief\n4. Draft Regulatory Submission Document\n"),
    md("## 1. Load All Prior Outputs"),
    code("import pandas as pd\nimport os\nos.makedirs('../outputs', exist_ok=True)\n\ndf_gaps = pd.read_csv('../outputs/regulatory_gap_analysis.csv')\ndf_fr = pd.read_csv('../outputs/functional_requirements.csv')\ndf_nfr = pd.read_csv('../outputs/non_functional_requirements.csv')\ndf_int_gaps = pd.read_csv('../outputs/integration_gap_analysis.csv')\ndf_scenarios = pd.read_csv('../outputs/test_scenario_register.csv')\n\nprint('Gaps:', len(df_gaps), '| FRs:', len(df_fr), '| NFRs:', len(df_nfr))\nprint('Integration gaps:', len(df_int_gaps), '| Test scenarios:', len(df_scenarios))\nprint()\nhigh = df_gaps[df_gaps['severity']=='High']\nprint('HIGH SEVERITY GAPS:', len(high))\nfor _, g in high.iterrows():\n    print(f'  {g[\"gap_id\"]} - {g[\"gap_name\"]}')"),
    md("## 2. Executive Summary - Draft\n\n> **Activity:** Review and edit the AI-generated summary below. Can Marcus Reid understand it in 3 minutes? No unexplained jargon. Specific consequences. Clear ask.\n> Use **Prompt 5.1** to generate a first draft.\n"),
    code("executive_summary = '''\nEXECUTIVE SUMMARY - DRAFT v1\nMeridian Financial - KYC/AML Onboarding Remediation\nPrepared: [Current Date] | For: Marcus Reid (CFO)\n\nTHE PROBLEM\nThe FCA has formally notified Meridian Financial (ref: FCA/ONB/2024/0471) of gaps in our\nclient onboarding process relating to Know Your Customer (KYC) and Anti-Money Laundering\n(AML) compliance controls. The FCA has given us 90 days to demonstrate a credible plan.\n\nOur discovery found 7 regulatory gaps across the onboarding process. The most serious\nexpose Meridian to FCA enforcement action including fines and, in a worst case, withdrawal\nof regulatory authorisation.\n\nWHAT WE FOUND\nThe onboarding process has significant gaps in compliance controls:\n- No automated identity verification: ID checks are done manually by email\n- No beneficial ownership data: we do not meet FCA MLR 2017 Reg 28 (criminal liability)\n- No automated PEP screening: checks are run by hand when Diana remembers\n- No compliance-grade audit log: sign-offs are conducted by email - not FCA-compliant\n- No automated sanctions screening: no screening against official sanctions lists\n\nWHAT WE ARE BUILDING\nSprint 1 (10 weeks): Fixes all HIGH severity gaps.\nDeliverables: mandatory BO declaration, automated PEP screening, ID evidence capture,\nautomated audit logging, client risk rating at application.\n\nEstimated build cost: GBP 80-120k. Third-party tooling: GBP 15-25k/year.\n\nWHY A THIRD-PARTY VENDOR?\nFor BO verification, we evaluated build vs. buy. We recommend a specialist BO platform\n(Kyckr or Enumacloud) because: (a) 1-2 weeks to integrate vs. 6-8 to build in-house,\n(b) provides automated Companies House coverage, (c) total cost is lower.\n\nRISK AND RESIDUAL RISK\nAfter Sprint 1: all HIGH severity gaps addressed. Residual risks:\n- Sprint 2 gaps (medium severity) not fully resolved - monitoring plan in place\n- Third-party vendor dependency - fallback manual procedures defined\n- Salesforce FSC and Microservice integration remains technically complex\n\nCONSEQUENCES OF INACTION\nIf we do not fix these gaps, the FCA can:\n- Fine us up to GBP 250M or 10% of global annual turnover\n- Require us to cease onboarding new clients\n- Initiate withdrawal of regulatory authorisation in serious cases\n\nRECOMMENDED ACTIONS\n1. Marcus approves Sprint 1 budget by [Date + 1 week]\n2. Sarah Chen confirms vendor selection by [Date + 2 weeks]\n3. Sprint kick-off: [Date]\n4. Interim FCA update: [Date + 4 weeks]\n5. Weekly sprint reviews for duration of Sprint 1\n'''\nprint(executive_summary)"),
